I had the pleasure of visiting Kulto al Pintxo somewhat late in the day, and to be honest, I wasn't sure they'd still be serving. To my surprise and delight, the staff welcomed me with genuine warmth and hospitality, which instantly set the tone for a very enjoyable visit.

The atmosphere is relaxed and unpretentious, with a cozy terrace where I was kindly allowed to enjoy a cigar‚Äîsomething I greatly appreciated. It's not every day you find a spot that combines attentive service with that kind of flexibility, especially as the evening winds down.

As for the food, it was simple but satisfying, with a focus on classic flavors and quality ingredients. The jam√≥n was excellent‚Äîflavorful, well-sliced, and served with care. The tapas were equally enjoyable, offering a nice range of textures and tastes that matched the casual elegance of the place. Each dish felt thoughtfully prepared and well-seasoned, in the spirit of true pintxo culture.

Overall, Kulto al Pintxo is a hidden gem in the heart of Santa Cruz‚Äîideal for a late bite, a relaxed drink, and the kind of service that makes you feel truly welcome. I highly recommend it for anyone seeking authentic Spanish tapas in a friendly, no-rush setting.
